All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddAppointmentController
    Responsible for the control of the form to add an appointment.
    AddCustomerController
    Responsible for the control of the form to add a controller.
    Appointment
    Represent an appointment that consists of appointment ID, title of the appointment, its title, description, location, type, start and end time, as well as customer, user, and contact associated with the appointment.
    AppointmentDao
    Represents a DAO for appointment table providing the functionality to get all appointments from the table, add, update, or delete an appointment as well as retrieve one by the ID.
    AppointmentListController
    Responsible for the control of the appointment list view.
    AppointmentsTypeMonth
    Responsible for generating and displaying the report on all the appointments grouped by the type and month
    Contact
    Represent a contact that consists of contact ID, its name and email.
    ContactDao
    Represents a DAO for contacts table providing the functionality to get all contacts from the table, add, update, or delete a contact as well as retrieve one by the ID.
    Country
    Represents a country that consists of country ID and name.
    CountryDao
    Represents a DAO for country table providing the functionality to get all countries from the table, add, update, or delete a country as well as retrieve one by the ID.
    Customer
    Represent a customer that consists of customer ID, its name, address, postal code, phone number, and division.
    CustomerDao
    Represents a DAO for customers table providing the functionality to get all customers from the table, add, update, or delete a customer as well as retrieve one by the ID.
    CustomerListController
    Responsible for the control of the customer list view.
    CustomersDivisionCountry
    Responsible for generating and displaying the report on all the customers grouped by their location (division and country)
    DAO<T>
    Represents an interface for the DAO pattern, provides getAll, add, update, and delete skeleton for the classes.
    DAOMain  
    DBCache
    Responsible for keeping the local cache of all the entries in the customer, appointment, user, firstleveldiv, country and contact tables.
    DBConnection
    Responsible for the connection to the database and helps maintaining connection when needed
    DivisionCountry
    Represents one row of customers data grouped by division and country of the location of the customer.
    FirstLevelDiv
    Represent a division that consists of division ID, its name and country.
    FirstLevelDivDao
    Represents a DAO for firstLevelDivs table providing the functionality to get all firstLevelDivs from the table, add, update, or delete an appointment as well as retrieve one by the ID.
    LoginController
    Responsible for the control of the login form.
    MainMenuController
    Responsible for the control of the main menu.
    TypeAndMonth
    Represents one row of appointment data grouped by type of the appointment in a given month.
    User
    Represent a user that consists of user ID, its name and password.
    UsersDao
    Represents a DAO for users table providing the functionality to get all users from the table, add, update, or delete an user as well as retrieve one by the ID.
